Catholic virtue ethics




Great Commandment; "On these two commandments hang all the law and the prophets." – Matthew 22:35-40



Theological virtues



Faith (Fides)
Hope (Spes)
Charity (Caritas)


Source: Paul the Apostle

1 Corinthians 13












Cardinal virtues



Prudence (Prudentia)
Justice (Iustitia)
Temperance (Temperantia)
Fortitude (Fortitudo)


Sources: Plato

Republic, Book IV


Cicero
Saint Ambrose
Saint Augustine of Hippo
Saint Thomas Aquinas





Seven heavenly virtues



Chastity (Castitas)
Temperance (Temperantia)
Charity (Caritas)
Diligence (Industria)
Patience (Patientia)
Kindness (Humanitas)
Humility (Humilitas)


Source: Church Fathers





Seven deadly sins



Lust (Luxuria)
Gluttony (Gula)
Greed (Avaritia)
Sloth (Acedia)
Wrath (Ira)
Envy (Invidia)
Pride (Superbia)


Source: Prudentius, Psychomachia


